[[File:Cheyenne_Wells,_Colorado_2011.jpg|thumb|Cheyenne Wells town limits (2011)]]

As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web |url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=January 31, 2008 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> of 2000, there were 1,010 people, 417 households, and 261 families residing in the town.  The population density was {{convert|974.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  There were 505 housing units at an average density of {{convert|487.2|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}.  The racial makeup of the town was 91.19% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.99% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.79% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.10% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 6.44% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.50% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 9.90% of the population.

There were 417 households, out of which 33.3% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 53.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 6.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 37.2% were non-families. 33.3% of all households were made up of individuals, and 13.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.38 and the average family size was 3.08.

27.2% of the population was under the age of 18, 8.1% from 18 to 24, 27.9% from 25 to 44, 20.8% from 45 to 64, and 15.9% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 38 years. For every 100 females, there were 100.0 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 99.7 males.

The median income for a household in the town was $36,563, and the median income for a family was $45,132. Males had a median income of $32,941 versus $23,077 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $18,840.  About 7.5% of families and 11.1% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 12.4% of those under age 18 and 12.2% of those age 65 or over.

